          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
              "aonid": 26,
              "game-obj": "Actions",
              "name": "Recall Knowledge",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Rare",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 11,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "size"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "36e474dd2f4c19b317214eccf55c8c77",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Medium",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 5 feet, *Reach (Tall):* 5 feet, *Reach (Long):* 5 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 217,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "f65db8141d9dbdd326c5985d985dd811",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Ghost",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 362",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core pg. 362",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core",
              "page": 362,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Lost souls that haunt the world as incorporeal undead are called ghosts.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 222,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "9069c05fc367b13d7cd78746f010c8a6",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "slowed",
              "aonid": 35,
              "game-obj": "Conditions",
              "name": "slowed",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "ghost touch",
              "aonid": 297,
              "game-obj": "Equipment",
              "name": "ghost touch",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Incorporeal",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 218,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "GM Core pg. 330",
                "aonid": 218,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "GM Core pg. 330",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "GM Core",
              "page": 330,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "An incorporeal creature or object has no physical form. It can pass through solid objects, including walls. When inside an object, an incorporeal creature can\u2019t perceive, attack, or interact with anything outside the object, and if it starts its turn in an object, it\u2019s slowed 1 until the end of its turn. A corporeal and an incorporeal creature can pass through one another, but they can\u2019t end their movement in each other\u2019s space.  \n  \nAn incorporeal creature can\u2019t attempt Strength-based checks against physical creatures or objects\u2014only against incorporeal ones\u2014unless those objects have the ghost touch property rune. Likewise, a corporeal creature can\u2019t attempt Strength-based checks against incorporeal creatures or objects.  \n  \nIncorporeal creatures usually have immunity to effects or conditions that require a physical body, like disease, poison, and precision damage. They usually have resistance against all damage (except force damage and damage from Strikes with the _ghost touch_ property rune), with double the resistance against non-magical damage.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 149,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "94858588d7c573ac8c5cda595ef3a931",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Spirit",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 461",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 461",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 461,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with this trait can affect creatures with spiritual essence and might deal spirit damage. A creature with this trait is defined by its spiritual essence. Spirit creatures often lack a material form.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 160,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "20f6f5f93a453f3006eb194c6d712042",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Undead",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Once living, these creatures were infused after death with void energy and soul-corrupting unholy magic. When reduced to 0 Hit Points, an undead creature is destroyed. Undead creatures are damaged by vitality energy and are healed by void energy, and don\u2019t benefit from healing vitality effects.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "holy",
              "aonid": 517,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "holy",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Unholy",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "7c548a9e0a2647c082989720b3de0a87",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Wood",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 463,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the wood trait conjure or manipulate wood. Those that manipulate wood have no effect in an area without wood. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of wood or have a connection to magical wood.  \n  \nThese planes consist of trees and other flora latticed in organic patterns. Wood planes are often perfectly constructed to match their desired purpose or environment but aren\u2019t usually outright hostile to visitors.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
